{"questionId":"5652","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The table summarizes some properties of graphite and graphene.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4636/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-10_om_11.17.29.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/01\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that graphene is over 1600 times stronger than graphite.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>Any one of these alternatives:</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{1.3 \\times {{10}^{11}}}}{{76 \\times {{10}^6}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.3</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>11</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>76</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>6</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>1.7 × 10<sup>3</sup>/1711</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 2</em></strong></p>\n<p>1600 × 76 × 10<sup>6</sup>&nbsp;= 1.2 × 10<sup>11</sup> <strong>«</strong>is less than tensile strength of graphene<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 3</em></strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{1.3 \\times {{10}^{11}}}}{{1600}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.3</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>11</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1600</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;=&nbsp;8.1 × 10<sup>7</sup> <strong>«</strong>is greater than upper end of tensile strength for&nbsp;graphite<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept any value in the range&nbsp;</em><em>1700–27 083. Answer may be&nbsp;</em><em>expressed in scientific notation or&nbsp;</em><em>otherwise.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept any value calculated which is&nbsp;</em><em>less than the graphene tensile strength&nbsp;</em><em>based on a value chosen from within&nbsp;</em><em>the 4.8</em><em>–</em><em>76 ×</em><em>&nbsp;</em><em>10</em><sup><em>6 </em></sup><em>range.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"5652","referenceCode":"18M.3.sl.TZ2.1a.ii","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Show that graphene is over 1600 times stronger than graphite.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Chemical bonding and structure","4.3 Covalent structures","Core","Topic 4: Chemical bonding and structure"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}